Just came in looking to get a drink before a concert and I was EXTREMELY disappointed. The bar tender came to serve me and my friend and then refused to serve me. The server continued to say “this doesn’t even look like you”. Yes I am newly 21, but with me saying that I am legally allowed to drink.He asked to see another id and when I found it in my purse a minute later he passed me several times ignoring me. After a few minutes of waiting, I asked to see a manager and there “wasn’t one on duty”. So, if you plan on going to this pub make sure to bring your drivers license, passport, birth certificate, and social security card or just plan on going somewhere different. Also pro tip, try wearing the exact shirt and jewelry you are wearing in the picture on your id. It may even help to practice the exact face on your id in the mirror a few times before leaving the house. You don’t want to confuse the server too much with a different outfit and facial expression. Also, sincere apologies to the bartender. I didn’t mean to waste your precious time with my business, won’t happen again. :)
